The paper proposes a new architecture for learning graphs using neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed architecture involves the use of tensors and transformations, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing methods and proposes a new approach, which is a characteristic of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on standard benchmarks, which is a common practice in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.SI).
